INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (54,'Following termination of this Agreement, the Receiving Party shall, at the direction of the Disclosing Party, either destroy or return to the Disclosing Party all documents, materials, and other tangible manifestations of the Disclosing Party’s Confidential Information and shall destroy any electronic or digital manifestations of the Disclosing Party’s Confidential Information, except that the Receiving Party may retain one copy of the Confidential Information solely for the purpose of monitoring its obligations under this Agreement.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (56,'Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, Provider shall not provide Polus with any Personally-Identifiable Information. For purposes of this Agreement, “Personally-Identifiable Information” is any information that, when used alone or combined with other data, may be used to identify individuals, including Provider employees, clients, suppliers, or other third parties and which includes, but is not limited to, an individual’s name, mailing address, email address, phone number, account information, title, birth date, gender, occupation, or other information that is unique to or permits identification of that individual.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (57,'Polus shall use the Data solely for the Purpose. Disclosure by Provider of its Data does not constitute a grant to Polus of any right or license to such Data, except as set forth herein.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (58,'Polus shall exert reasonable efforts, including but not limited to the Data Safeguards identified in Attachment A, to maintain Data in confidence, except that Polus may disclose or permit disclosure of any Data to members of the Polus Corporation and Polus’s officers, faculty, employees, consultants, advisors, students and fellows who need to know such Data to fulfill the Purpose and who have been advised of the confidential nature of the Data. Polus will not be deemed to have disclosed Data if the Data, when disclosed, is aggregated with data or other information and cannot be reconstituted from the aggregate form.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (59,'Polus shall not identify Provider as the source of the Data in any publication or public presentation of research results for which Data are used (each a “Publication”) without obtaining Provider’s prior written consent.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (60,'Nothing in this Agreement may be construed to prevent Polus from disclosing Data as required by law or legal process, as long as Polus, if permitted by applicable law, promptly notifies Provider of its obligation to disclose and provides reasonable cooperation to Provider in any efforts to contest or limit the scope of the disclosure.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (62,'Provider shall not make any press or media announcements concerning this Agreement, or use Polus’s names, trademarks, logos, or insignia, or any version, abbreviation, or representation of them, or the name of any of Polus’s trustees, officers, faculty members, students, employees, or agents, in any advertising, publicity, promotional materials or other public announcement without the prior written consent of Polus’s Institute Office of Communications (ioc-useofname@mit.edu), which consent Polus may withhold in its sole discretion.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (63,'Either party may terminate this Agreement, with or without cause, by providing at least thirty (30) day’s prior written notice to the other party. Polus’s obligations with respect to nondisclosure of Data will survive until the End Date, or any earlier termination or extension thereof.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (64,'Following expiration (the End Date) or termination of this Agreement, Polus shall, as directed by Provider, undertake reasonable efforts to destroy or return to Provider all documents and other tangible manifestations of Data and destroy any electronic or digital manifestations of Data.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
INSERT INTO CLAUSES_BANK (`CLAUSES_CODE`,`DESCRIPTION`,`UPDATE_TIMESTAMP`,`UPDATE_USER`) VALUES (65,'Any notices to be given under this Agreement must be in writing and addressed to the parties at the addresses shown below or to such other address as a party may substitute by notice to the other. Notices must be sent by commercial courier, such as FedEx or DHL, via express, priority or similar service and will be deemed to have been given on the next business day following tender to the courier if the sender’s and recipient’s addresses are in same country or on the fourth business day following tender to the courier if the addresses are in different countries.',UTC_TIMESTAMP(),'admin');
